                <h1>Easy Tips for Hanging Peel and Stick Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>To hang peel and stick wallpaper successfully, start with a clean, smooth surface. Measure and cut your wallpaper strips, leaving a bit of excess. Peel back a small section of the adhesive and align it at the top. Smooth downwards with a credit card to remove air bubbles. Use a sharp blade to trim edges for a perfect finish.</p>
